[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 218 (Samoa has not been added).

Data by country, area, or territory for 1 Dec 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesDEC1%20(1)_1606865705.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 46.7% of daily case numbers and 24.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours but maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 26.6 million cases. The USA continues to dominate, followed by Brazil, Colombia, Mexico, Canada, Argentina, and Peru. Other countries reporting more than 1000 cases include Chile and Panama. And countries/territories reporting more than 500 cases but fewer than 1000 in the past 24 hours include Puerto Rico, Paraguay, Ecuador, and Dominican Republic. Costa Rica did not report any new confirmed cases in the past 48 hours.

- The European region reported 34.1% of daily case numbers and 54.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 18.8 million. Countries not reporting cases today (1 Dec 2020) include Spain, Sweden, and Kazakhstan, among others. Countries reporting more than 10 000 cases in the past 24 hours include Russia, Italy, Germany, Ukraine, and the UK. 22 additional countries are reporting more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 7.3% of daily case numbers and 9.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 4.11 million cases. Iran is dominant, with continuing highs above 10 000, followed by Jordan, Pakistan, Morocco, Iraq, Palestinian Authority, UAE, and Lebanon. Yemen and Somalia have not reported any cases in the past 24 hours.

- The African region reported 1.4% of daily case numbers and 1.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.50 million cases. South Africa maintains its dominance, followed by Algeria, Ethiopia, Kenya, Uganda, and Nigeria.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 0.57% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.88 million cases. Japan is dominant, followed by Philippines, Malaysia, South Korea, French Polynesia, China, and Guam.

- The South East Asia region reported 9.2% of the daily newly reported cases and 9.1% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.8 million cases. As previously, India remains dominant, followed by Indonesia, Bangladesh, Myanmar, and Nepal. Bhutan had a 3.5% increase with reports of 14 new cases.

Impression: Basically unchanged on the regional levels with the continued dominance of Europe and the Americas region representing over 80% of newly confirmed cases and 79% of newly reported deaths in the past 24 hours, even with continued reduced reports from the weekend. At the country level, Japan is the dominant country in the Western Pacific region; Italy and Russia are dominant in the European region. The USA maintains its position as the country reporting the most cases on a daily basis.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 1 Dec 2020, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.MPP]

