[In the past 24 hours, the USA (188 620), Brazil (52 248), India (36 456), Turkey (30 110), and Russia (26 402) have reported the highest numbers of cases and represent 55.3% of all newly confirmed cases reported in the past 24 hours. A global total of 12 868 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (30 Nov 2020-1 Dec 2020). Countries not reporting newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours include Ghana, Nepal, Tunisia, and Venezuela, among others.

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (11 countries) include the USA, Brazil, India, Turkey, Russia, Italy (19 347), Sweden (17 629), Germany (15 898), Iran (13 881), UK (13 429), and Ukraine (12 498). A total of 58 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (down from 64 on Fri 27 Nov 2020); 32 of the 58 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 10 are from the Americas region, 8 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 1 is from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days (584 178) and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 1.7%, while daily reported deaths (10 284) have increased by 0.73%. The USA has decreased both newly confirmed cases (-8.4%) and reported deaths (-4.7%) which may still be a function of the weekend decreased reporting. The 7-day average daily new cases reported in the USA is 164 783 and newly reported deaths is 1584.

Impression: The countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean and the South East Asia regions. Globally the 64 million reported case mark has been crossed; Poland will cross the 1 million cumulative case count tomorrow as the 13th country reporting more than 1 million cases; and the state of Florida in the USA has crossed the 1 million cumulative case count in the past 24 hours, making it the 3rd state in the USA to report more than 1 million cases. - Mod.MPP]
